qas.question: What type of radio stations abound in Seattle?
What are KUOW and KPLU radio stations?
With what educational facility is KEXP-FM aligned?
What radio station is operated by the public school system?
Where has KEXP pioneered in Radio?

context: <a0_0>Non-commercial<a0_0/> radio stations include <a1_0>NPR affiliates<a1_0/> KUOW-FM 94.9 and KPLU-FM 88.5 (Tacoma), as well as classical music station KING-FM 98.1. Other stations include KEXP-FM 90.3 (affiliated with the <a2_0>UW<a2_0/>), community radio KBCS-FM 91.3 (affiliated with Bellevue College), and high school radio <a3_0>KNHC-FM 89.5<a3_0/>, which broadcasts an electronic dance music radio format and is owned by the public school system and operated by students of Nathan Hale High School. Many Seattle radio stations are also available through Internet radio, with KEXP in particular being a pioneer of <a4_0>Internet radio<a4_0/>. Seattle also has numerous commercial radio stations. In a March 2012 report by the consumer research firm Arbitron, the top FM stations were KRWM (adult contemporary format), KIRO-FM (news/talk), and KISW (active rock) while the top AM stations were KOMO (AM) (all news), KJR (AM) (all sports), KIRO (AM) (all sports).
